<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="H" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Hermit" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Hermit,</orth> 1) an anchoret: <bibl n="shak. lll 4.3.242" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL IV, 3, 242</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 5.33" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. V, 33</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 4.2.15" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. IV, 2, 15</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h4 5.1.71" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B V, 1, 71</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h6 2.5.117" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A II, 5, 117</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tro 5.3.45" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. V, 3, 45</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 3.2.41" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. III, 2, 41</bibl>.<lb />2) a beadsman, one bound to pray for another: <cit><quote>we rest your --s,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 1.6.20" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. I, 6, 20</bibl></cit>; cf. <bibl n="shak. tit 3.2.41" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. III, 2, 41</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>